items.title: SBI Q1 results: Net profit up 12% driven by treasury gains, retail loan growth
items.description: State Bank of India (SBI) surpassed D-Street expectations with a 12% increase in its June-quarter net profit, reaching ₹19,160 crore. This growth was primarily driven by higher treasury income and expansion in retail loans. The bank benefited from gains on government securities sales due to policy rate cuts and increased foreign exchange trading income.
